  "title": "LORRY DRIVER",
  "description": "<p>Core Responsibilities</p>\n<ul>\n  <li><strong>Vehicle Operation:</strong>Safely driving large commercial vehicles, such as trucks, tankers, and articulated lorries, over varying distances.</li>\n  <li><strong>Vehicle Maintenance:</strong>Conducting daily pre-trip and post-trip vehicle inspections, checking vital components like tires, oil, and brakes, and reporting any mechanical issues.</li>\n  <li><strong>Loading and Securing Cargo:</strong>Overseeing and assisting with the safe loading and unloading of goods, ensuring they are properly secured to prevent damage during transit.</li>\n  <li><strong>Route Planning:</strong>Planning and adapting delivery routes to meet schedules, while also monitoring traffic reports to avoid delays.</li>\n  <li><strong>Documentation:</strong>Completing and maintaining accurate delivery records, logbooks, and trip reports.</li>\n  <li><strong>Compliance:</strong>Adhering to all road haulage regulations, company policies, and procedures, including rules on driving hours, vehicle weight, and safety standards.</li>\n</ul>",
